cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about image segmentation using machine learning algorithms. The paper discusses the use of a classifier to predict an affinity graph that reflects the degree to which image pixels must be grouped together and then partitioned to yield a segmentation. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the Rand index, which is a well-known segmentation performance measure, indicating that it could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
